==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from Old French [[baffe]] ‘slap in the face’ (French [[bouffe]]), of imitative origin.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /bæf/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æf|-æf]]

===Verb===
'''baff'''
# to [[hit]] or [[strike]], especially with something flat or soft
# ''(Golf)'' to strike the ground with the bottom of the [[club]] when taking a stroke

